SIMPLE: emblaze
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emblaze
<hw>Em*blaze"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Emblazed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Emblazing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>em-</ets>
+ 1st <ets>blaze</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To adorn with glittering
embellishments.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No weeping orphan saw his father's stores⟦br⟧
Our shrines irradiate, or <qex>emblaze</qex> the floors.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To paint or adorn with armorial figures; to blazon,
or emblazon.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The imperial ensign, . . . streaming to the wind,⟦br⟧
With gems and golden luster rich <qex>emblazed</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emblazon</ent>⟦br⟧
